# ü•Å Project - Interactive Drum Kit

This project consists of an interactive drum kit built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.  
The application allows sound playback through clicks on visual buttons or keyboard navigation,  
using modern web development practices.

---

## üìö Learnings

### 0. Functions
- Created JavaScript functions to play sounds stored in `<audio>` elements in the HTML.

### 1. Interactivity
- Implemented buttons using HTML and CSS that play the corresponding sound when clicked.

### 2. Keyboard Navigation
- Accessibility feature implemented: sound playback when pressing `Enter` or `Space` on a focused button.

### 3. Optimized Code
- Reduced code repetition through function reuse.
- Improved organization and maintainability of the code.

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Technologies Used

### 1. JavaScript Functions
- Used functions to encapsulate the logic for sound playback and interaction.

### 2. DOM Manipulation
- Accessed and modified HTML elements using `document.querySelector` and `addEventListener`.

### 3. Control Flow
- Applied loops and conditionals (`for`, `if`) to handle logic across multiple elements.
